币和财政刺激来应对。这个基本公式——称之为新自由主义/社会民主混合经济——创造了地球上 <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_Development_Index#/media/File:HDI2022Incrimental.svg">最高度发达</a>和<a href="https://www.visualcapitalist.com/a-map-of-global-happiness-by-country-in-2024/">最幸福的</a>社会。如果你想让政府介入并开始改变一个国家的产业结构，从而破坏这个公式，那么你需要一个充分的理由。</p><p>美国和我们的民主盟友有一个<em>很好</em>的理由：<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/in-which-british-writers-scold-america">国家安全</a>。中俄轴心要求民主国家重建和增强自己的制造业，而这需要以某种方式干预自由市场。产业政策是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/economy/the-u-s-finally-has-a-strategy-to-compete-with-china-will-it-work-ce4ea6cf">其中的重要组成部分</a>。</p><p>但这些国家安全担忧直到过去五年才真正变得普遍。美国经济思维的转变实际上早<em>在</em>这之前就已经开始了。我记得 2017 年，我参加了彭博社的一次会议，会上几乎所有人——主要是一群来自科技、智库和媒体的进步知识分子——都在谈论恢复产业政策的必要性。但中国从未被提及——每个人都引用的最大理由是<em>气候变化</em>。</p><p>我记得听到每个人都在谈论应对气候变化如何需要像第二次世界大战那样的工业动员——建设绿色能源、转向电动汽车、改造我们的工业流程以及改装或重建建筑物。而且市场的发展速度还不够快。就像 2010 年的吉米·卡特一样，我的朋友们在 2010 年也相信能源转型<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moral_Equivalent_of_War_speech">在道德上等同于战争</a>。</p><p>这个想法一路进入了拜登政府。在拜登的三项标志性工业政策法案中，其中两项——《减少通货膨胀法案》和《基础设施法案》——主要旨在促进绿色能源产业以应对气候变化。 2010年代的进步知识分子取得了胜利。</p><p>但现在，随着拜登对中国电动汽车、电池和太阳能电池板征收新关税，剧本发生了一些逆转。许多为绿色产业政策兴起而欢呼的进步思想家对美国将提高绿色科技产品的价格感到沮丧。例如， <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2024-05-28/biden-s-tariffs-on-china-evs-delay-clean-energy-worsen-climate-change?utm_source=website&amp;utm_medium=share&amp;utm_campaign=twitter">大卫·菲克林写道</a>：</p><blockquote><p>政府已承诺投入数千亿美元来加速向电动汽车的过渡。然而，为了阻止进口激增，它最近<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-05-14/biden-imposes-sweeping-tariffs-on-chinese-chips-minerals-evs">宣布</a>对中国制造的电动汽车征收 100% 的关税，从而推迟了它正确地坚持认为至关重要的转型。</p><p>拜登和他的官员似乎很困惑。他们可以将应对气候变化作为首要任务，或者将保护美国生产商免受外国竞争作为首要目标。他们不能两者兼而有之……</p><p>最后，事情并没有那么复杂：如果气候变化是一种生存风险，那么优质、廉价的中国电动汽车产量激增是一件好事。</p></blockquote><p>迪伦·马修斯 (Dylan Matthews) 在三月份也<a href="https://www.vox.com/climate/2024/3/4/24087919/biden-tariff-chinese-ev-byd-battery-detroit">提出过类似的论点</a>：</p><blockquote><p> [中国电动汽车]绝对是令人尖叫的交易——正是那种可以加速我们从汽油汽车向<a href="https://www.vox.com/electric-vehicles">电动汽车</a>过渡的产品……美国人面临的问题是什么？<a href="https://www.vox.com/joe-biden">拜登政府</a>铁了心要阻止你购买比亚迪的产品，如果<a href="https://www.vox.com/donald-trump">唐纳德·特朗普</a>重新上任，他也可能会与之抗争。</p><p>这是因为比亚迪汽车是在中国制造的，拜登和特朗普都致力于极端民族主义贸易政策，旨在将比亚迪的产品拒之门外……中国电动汽车案例很好地证明了，无论拜登政府的动机可能是出于气候问题，<em>更大的</em>动机是帮助美国汽车制造商，赢得今年11月密歇根州的选举人票，以及升级正在酝酿的针对中国的冷战……事实证明，如果它坚持与中国合作，它会非常愿意破坏自己的气候政策正在进行中。</p></blockquote><p> <a href="https://thehill.com/policy/energy-environment/4670967-joe-biden-china-tariffs-risk-downgrading-energy-transition/">其他人也</a><a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/opinions/2024/05/16/china-tariffs-climate-evs-energy/">赞同</a>这一论点。</p><p>如果气候变化确实是美国经济政策发生重大变化的主要原因，那么菲克林和马修斯是对的，美国理应听从他们的建议。但不管我的许多朋友和同事在 2017 年的想法如何，气候变化实际上<em>并不是</em>产业政策的主要原因，未来也不会如此。所以他们对着风喊叫。</p><p>造成这种情况的原因不仅仅是因为国家安全问题在美国精英的心目中占据优先地位——尽管这确实是事实。由于许多其他原因，气候变化不适合成为美国经济政策变化的主要驱动力。在民意方面，它并不能激励公众投票，而且两党合作的可能性也较低。与此同时，廉价的中国进口产品可能不会成为绿色能源转型的关键因素。</p><p>因此，虽然气候政策很重要，但它不能独立存在。相反，它必须只是旨在重振美国工业实力的一系列政策的一部分。</p><h4>气候变化是真实且重要的，但它并不能激励选民</h4><p>任何否认人为气候变化的现实和重要性的人都将被<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/a-bunch-of-handy-charts-about-climate">牢牢地堵在耳朵里</a>。气温<a href="https://www.economist.com/graphic-detail/2024/01/12/eight-charts-illustrate-2023s-extreme-weather">稳步上升</a>，年复一年地创下有记录以来最热的纪录： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F131bc157-fc0b-4cc8-a690-923a225a5594_1638x737.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F131bc157-fc0b-4cc8-a690-923a225a5594_1638x737.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F131bc157-fc0b-4cc8-a690-923a225a5594_1638x737.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F131bc157-fc0b-4cc8-a690-923a225a5594_1638x737.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F131bc157-fc0b-4cc8-a690-923a225a5594_1638x737.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F131bc157-fc0b-4cc8-a690-923a225a5594_1638x737.jpeg" width="1456" height="655" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/131bc157-fc0b-4cc8-a690-923a225a5594_1638x737.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:655,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:325279,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F131bc157-fc0b-4cc8-a690-923a225a5594_1638x737.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F131bc157-fc0b-4cc8-a690-923a225a5594_1638x737.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F131bc157-fc0b-4cc8-a690-923a225a5594_1638x737.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F131bc157-fc0b-4cc8-a690-923a225a5594_1638x737.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">来源： <a href="https://x.com/hausfath/status/1763992079477379514/">Zeke Hausfather</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>对于美国、加拿大和澳大利亚等富裕国家来说，气候变化的危害表现为<a href="https://nintil.com/wildfires-california/">野火风险增加</a>和<a href="https://www.bbc.com/future/article/20240311-why-climate-change-is-making-the-us-uninsurable">沿海洪水风险增加</a>。对于印度等许多贫穷的赤道国家来说，它表现为<a href="https://www.reuters.com/world/india/indias-capital-sees-first-heat-related-death-this-year-media-reports-2024-05-30/">难以忍受的热浪</a>，导致供水短缺，<a href="https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c166xxd4y36o">使城市环境变得不适宜居住</a>。更糟糕的情况还在后面——<a href="https://x.com/hausfath/status/1755681397229113836">模型预测</a>和<a href="https://x.com/hausfath/status/1788588264179593496">共识预测</a>本世纪气候将升温约 2.7°C（这是一个很大的数字），而即使全球做出巨大努力，情况仍然会变得更糟。所以请抓紧你的帽子——这将是<a href="https://www.economist.com/films/2021/10/30/this-is-what-3degc-of-global-warming-looks-like">一段坎坷的旅程</a>。</p><p>所以每个人都<em>应该</em>非常关心气候变化。但我说那不会是这样。不幸的事实是，尽管有数十年的激进主义和精英言论，但投票公众并没有高度重视气候问题。马特·伊格莱西亚斯在一月份解释了这一点： </p><div class="embedded-post-wrap" data-attrs="{&quot;id&quot;:140589619,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.slowboring.com/p/climate-is-the-problem&quot;,&quot;publication_id&quot;:159185,&quot;publication_name&quot;:&quot;Slow Boring &quot;,&quot;publication_logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fceeb681e-a14d-4bbb-a8fe-951c29603e3f_256x256.png&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Climate is the problem&quot;,&quot;truncated_body_text&quot;:&quot;Center-left intellectuals like me have two passions in life: complaining about the things that we, personally, find annoying about far-left ideologues and wringing our hands about the electoral fortunes of the Democratic Party. Sometimes these two things coincide. We tend to live in urban areas, so we worried on a personal level about the spike in crime in 2020-2021 and (correctly) warned of the political risks of embracing soft-on-crime policies. But we are fallible and at times fall prey to the very human tendency to project our picayune concerns onto persuadable voters, while ignoring voter concerns that don&#8217;t line up with our own. And while insofar as &#8220;woke&#8221; politics leads to rising murders, that&#8217;s a very real political problem. And my sense is that a lot of people in my broad political space over-index on the idea that&quot;,&quot;date&quot;:&quot;2024-01-16T11:00:42.376Z&quot;,&quot;like_count&quot;:332,&quot;comment_count&quot;:580,&quot;bylines&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:580004,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Matthew Yglesias&quot;,&quot;handle&quot;:&quot;matthewyglesias&quot;,&quot;previous_name&quot;:null,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/20964455-401a-494d-a8ef-9835b34e9809_3024x3024.png&quot;,&quot;bio&quot;:&quot;Blogger, journalist, podcaster, trying to get back to my roots. &quot;,&quot;profile_set_up_at&quot;:&quot;2021-04-21T11:11:05.347Z&quot;,&quot;publicationUsers&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:18017,&quot;user_id&quot;:580004,&quot;publication_id&quot;:159185,&quot;role&quot;:&quot;admin&quot;,&quot;public&quot;:true,&quot;is_primary&quot;:false,&quot;publication&quot;:{&quot;id&quot;:159185,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Slow Boring &quot;,&quot;subdomain&quot;:&quot;matthewyglesias&quot;,&quot;custom_domain&quot;:&quot;www.slowboring.com&quot;,&quot;custom_domain_optional&quot;:false,&quot;hero_text&quot;:&quot;Start your day with pragmatic takes on politics and public policy.&quot;,&quot;logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/ceeb681e-a14d-4bbb-a8fe-951c29603e3f_256x256.png&quot;,&quot;author_id&quot;:580004,&quot;theme_var_background_pop&quot;:&quot;#121BFA&quot;,&quot;created_at&quot;:&quot;2020-11-05T16:20:32.177Z&quot;,&quot;rss_website_url&quot;:null,&quot;email_from_name&quot;:&quot;Matthew Yglesias&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;Matthew Yglesias&quot;,&quot;founding_plan_name&quot;:&quot;Charismatic Authority&quot;,&quot;community_enabled&quot;:true,&quot;invite_only&quot;:false,&quot;payments_state&quot;:&quot;enabled&quot;,&quot;language&quot;:null,&quot;explicit&quot;:false}}],&quot;twitter_screen_name&quot;:&quot;mattyglesias&quot;,&quot;is_guest&quot;:false,&quot;bestseller_tier&quot;:10000}],&quot;utm_campaign&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;newsletter&quot;,&quot;language&quot;:&quot;en&quot;}" data-component-name="EmbeddedPostToDOM"><a class="embedded-post" native="true" href="https://www.slowboring.com/p/climate-is-the-problem?utm_source=substack&amp;utm_campaign=post_embed&amp;utm_medium=web"><div class="embedded-post-header"><img class="embedded-post-publication-logo" src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_56,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fceeb681e-a14d-4bbb-a8fe-951c29603e3f_256x256.png" loading="lazy"><span class="embedded-post-publication-name">慢镗</span></div><div class="embedded-post-title-wrapper"><div class="embedded-post-title">气候是问题</div></div><div class="embedded-post-body">像我这样的中左翼知识分子在生活中有两种热情：抱怨我们个人认为极左思想家讨厌的事情，以及为民主党的选举命运而绞尽脑汁。有时这两件事是一致的。我们往往生活在城市地区，因此我们对 2020-2021 年犯罪率激增感到担忧，并（正确地）警告了采取温和打击犯罪政策的政治风险。但我们也容易犯错，有时会陷入一种人类倾向，即把我们的小事担忧投射到可说服的选民身上，而忽视选民与我们自己不一致的担忧。虽然“觉醒”的政治会导致谋杀案上升，但这是一个非常现实的政治问题。我的感觉是，在我广阔的政治空间中，很多人过度关注以下想法……</div><div class="embedded-post-cta-wrapper"><span class="embedded-post-cta">阅读更多</span></div><div class="embedded-post-meta">5 个月前 · 332 个赞 · 580 条评论 · 马修·伊格莱西亚斯</div></div><p>一些摘录：</p><blockquote><p>如果你稍微探究一下公众舆论，就会发现公众对气候行动的支持是一英里宽、一英寸深。例如，益普索 (IPSOS) 发现， <a href="https://www.ipsos.com/sites/default/files/ct/news/documents/2023-04/Ipsos%20Global%20Advisor%20-%20Earth%20Day%202023%20-%20Full%20Report%20-%20WEB.pdf">只有 25% 的美国人表示他们愿意缴纳更高的税</a>来应对气候变化。路透社 2019 年的一项民意调查特别询问了受访者是否愿意支付 100 美元来应对气候变化，<a href="https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSKCN1TR17X/">只有三分之一的人表示愿意</a>。您愿意每月多支付 10 美元的电费来应对气候变化吗？ <a href="https://www.cato.org/blog/68-americans-wouldnt-pay-10-month-higher-electric-bills-combat-climate-change">大多数人都说不</a>。</p></blockquote><p>如果选民相信气候变化的重要性，也许这种情况可能会改变。但多年来，活动人士一直表现得极为尖锐，虽然这似乎有助于提高精英阶层的认识（这很好！），但它却未能使气候变化成为公众中的热门事业。现在，气候活动人士——至少是那些没有<a href="https://www.aljazeera.com/program/newsfeed/2023/11/13/man-grabs-mic-from-greta-thunberg-at-climate-rally">转向巴勒斯坦的</a>人——正集中<a href="https://x.com/ZombiePanther2/status/1796002740121833614">精力抨击民主党</a>，搞一些<a href="https://news.artnet.com/art-world/here-is-every-artwork-attacked-by-climate-activists-this-year-from-the-mona-lisa-to-girl-with-a-pearl-earring-2200804">不受欢迎的噱头</a>，并提出<a href="https://x.com/RogerHallamCS21/status/1795734145223545338">越来越可怕的说法</a>，比如“亚利桑那州凤凰城的 12% 的人口将死于气候变化”。 2030 年代极端炎热。”</p><p>它就是行不通。选民<em>应该</em>关心，但他们坚决拒绝关心。几十年来，民主党人一直在言论中强调气候变化，而美国人仍然没有准备好向化石燃料宣战。</p><p>与此同时，虽然共和党的很大一部分人都同意对抗中国的需要，但气候问题往往会激发他们的党派本能。虽然一些共和党人确实支持基础设施法案和其他一些促进电动汽车发展的小法案，但<em>零票</em>支持规模大得多的《通货膨胀削减法案》。民意调查显示，电动汽车已成为文化战争的焦点——自由派强烈支持电动汽车，而保守派<a href="https://www.wsj.com/business/autos/another-roadblock-to-the-ev-transition-personal-politics-ab4e311b">则以二比一的比例不赞成电动汽车</a>。</p><p>国家经济政策的转变需要双方共同参与——通常不是通过两党合作，而是通过竞争在基本范式上打上自己的印记。艾森豪威尔和尼克松都在新政中留下了自己的印记，而<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/repost-much-of-what-youve-heard-about">卡特</a>和克林顿则实施了“新自由主义”革命的关键部分。大多数民主党人和大多数共和党人肯定都支持国家安全，并且都了解产业政策在该领域的重要性。但共和党干脆拒绝将气候政策作为美国经济的指导方向。</p><p>因此，气候变化仍将存在分歧。这不会使气候政策成为不可能，但会阻止它成为经济政策制定的核心、压倒一切的要务。</p><p>幸运的是，并不需要如此。</p><h4>即使气候并不总是第一要务，绿色能源转型也会发生</h4><p>减少美国排放量的收益虽然不大，但绝非微不足道。<a href="https://x.com/sam_d_1995/status/1796161948632895858">一些分析发现</a>，与特朗普的政策相比，拜登的经济政策将导致到2030年减少约17亿吨二氧化碳当量排放。这大约占<a href="https://ourworldindata.org/co2-emissions">2022 年全球排放量的 4.6%</a> ——这个数字虽然不是很大，但也不是没有。在应对气候变化方面，中国仍然比美国更重要（而且有<a href="https://x.com/AssaadRazzouk/status/1795610609847013886">希望的迹象表明中国现在做得更好</a>），但美国当然可以提供很多帮助。</p><p>以下是美国温室气体排放的来源： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7304bfc6-e980-47a7-ad47-0edf0727c123_393x389.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7304bfc6-e980-47a7-ad47-0edf0727c123_393x389.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7304bfc6-e980-47a7-ad47-0edf0727c123_393x389.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7304bfc6-e980-47a7-ad47-0edf0727c123_393x389.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7304bfc6-e980-47a7-ad47-0edf0727c123_393x389.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7304bfc6-e980-47a7-ad47-0edf0727c123_393x389.jpeg" width="393" height="389" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/7304bfc6-e980-47a7-ad47-0edf0727c123_393x389.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:389,&quot;width&quot;:393,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:29337,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7304bfc6-e980-47a7-ad47-0edf0727c123_393x389.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7304bfc6-e980-47a7-ad47-0edf0727c123_393x389.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7304bfc6-e980-47a7-ad47-0edf0727c123_393x389.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F7304bfc6-e980-47a7-ad47-0edf0727c123_393x389.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：<a href="https://www.epa.gov/ghgemissions/sources-greenhouse-gas-emissions">美国环保局</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>为了脱碳，我们需要做好以下四件事：</p><ol><li><p>转向绿色能源——主要是由电池存储支持的太阳能，但也有一些核能和风能</p></li><li><p>改用电动汽车、公共汽车和其他车辆</p></li><li><p>家庭供暖（和烹饪）通电</p></li><li><p>使钢铁和水泥等一系列工业流程电气化，或使用其他绿色替代品</p></li></ol><p>基本上，您可以将其归结为 1）使一切电气化，2）确保电网本身使用绿色能源。</p><p>幸运的是，两种神奇的技术已经出现，使这两项任务比 2010 年或 1990 年要容易<em>得多</em>。太阳能和电池正处于陡峭的学习曲线上——随着我们生产越来越多的太阳能和电池，它们的价格也越来越高。呈指数级下降。因此，太阳能的扩张速度比历史上任何能源技术都要快： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35b2f9ec-3a0c-4343-801e-5bcbb61722de_937x528.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35b2f9ec-3a0c-4343-801e-5bcbb61722de_937x528.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35b2f9ec-3a0c-4343-801e-5bcbb61722de_937x528.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35b2f9ec-3a0c-4343-801e-5bcbb61722de_937x528.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35b2f9ec-3a0c-4343-801e-5bcbb61722de_937x528.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35b2f9ec-3a0c-4343-801e-5bcbb61722de_937x528.jpeg" width="937" height="528" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/35b2f9ec-3a0c-4343-801e-5bcbb61722de_937x528.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:528,&quot;width&quot;:937,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:56787,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35b2f9ec-3a0c-4343-801e-5bcbb61722de_937x528.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35b2f9ec-3a0c-4343-801e-5bcbb61722de_937x528.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35b2f9ec-3a0c-4343-801e-5bcbb61722de_937x528.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35b2f9ec-3a0c-4343-801e-5bcbb61722de_937x528.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2 "><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源：<a href="https://www.nathanielbullard.com/presentations">纳特·布拉德</a></figcaption></figure></div><p><a href="https://ember-climate.org/insights/research/global-electricity-review-2024/">Ember 最近的一份报告</a>发现，太阳能和风能目前约占全球电力的 12%——这是实际发电量，而不是“容量”。如果将其添加到现有的水力发电中，可再生能源现在发电量约占世界电力的 30%，并且还在快速增长： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a3606fd-46c7-44be-a595-82c39b0c816c_1232x763.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a3606fd-46c7-44be-a595-82c39b0c816c_1232x763.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a3606fd-46c7-44be-a595-82c39b0c816c_1232x763.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a3606fd-46c7-44be-a595-82c39b0c816c_1232x763.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a3606fd-46c7-44be-a595-82c39b0c816c_1232x763.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F6a3606fd-46c7-44